author: National Geographic
description:
The internet is convinced that orange cats are just, well, goofier than other kinds of cats. National Geographic contributor Jason Bittel explains what the current science says about ginger cats and whether their wackiness is in their genes or just in our heads. 🐈 

Learn more about orange cats and the scientific search for the source of their goofiness: https://on.natgeo.com/4mWFte2

author: National Geographic
description:
Celebrate the back to school season with this inspiring mega episode of Science Fair: the Series. In this full episode compilation, students from around the globe compete for a coveted seat at the world's most competitive science fair, the International Scientific and Engineering Fair (ISEF), by using science to tackle some of the most difficult and urgent problems facing society today. Which young scientists have what it takes?

The Games Begin
Students begin an intense journey to ISEF - but before they can advance to the international science stage, they'll have to compete in local fairs. 

Judgment Day
As qualifying science fair season begins for students in Monte Vista, CO and San Juan, PR who hope this will be their year to make it to ISEF. 

The Big Dance
Welcome to ISEF - the International Science and Engineering Fair. Out of 2,000 students, who will make it?

Science Fair: the Series  | S1, E1-3
